content.description: No. 5 on the beta photo.  Not sure if this has been done or is even worth doing.  Start sitting and climb the right arete of the wall.  A small boulder on the right makes it very awkward and dabby...

No. 4 on the beta photo. Start sitting matched on a crimp approximately 3 feet right of the obvious jug.  Jug and crack/seam on the left are off-route.  Climb cool crimps on the face to a good hold on shelf then get high foot and step up onto the shelf.  Still some slab climbing to get to the top (avoid the small trees).  Needs a bit more cleaning.

No. 1 in the beta photo, start almost sitting on a big shelf.  Follow the left edge of the wall up and right to a juggy topout.  After topping the wall, you must still climb a kind of dirty slab to get off the wall.  Could use more cleaning.

No. 3 on the beta photo.  Climb the obvious crack/seam from a sit start.  Jug and right facing corner mark the start and any and all holds are on.  Topout as for Left Line and Cool Holds at the peak of the wall.
No. 2 on the beta photo.  Start sitting with crimps (good for right, bad for left) left of the jug and crack (which are off-route).  Climb the face left of the crack to the same topout as Left Line.

This wall is somewhat hidden on the left side (when heading towards the Sit Down area) at the bottom of the hill after the egg.  The wall faces away from the road and is kind of a surprise when you walk around the back of the lump of rock you can see from the road.
